What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main()
{
    int a{ 010 };
    int b{ 0x10 };
    int c{ 0b10 };
    std::cout << a << " " << b << " " << c << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

The programmer wants `big` to hold the value 10,000,000,000 (ten billion). What is wrong?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main()
{
    long long big{ 10000000000 };
    std::cout << big << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

